nce of Beauvoir's philosophy and life on her own work and career. These innovative essays both broaden our understanding of Beauvoir and suggest new ways of understanding canonical figures through the lens of her work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aBeauvoir, Simone de, -- 1908-1986. 0aPhilosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Feminist Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : History of Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Literature. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh1 aBergoffen, Debra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinämaa, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHooks, Bell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcbride, William L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMccarthy, Erin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Elaine P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurphy, Ann V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMussett, Shannon M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMussett, Shannon M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aScholz, Sally J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimons, Margaret A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeiss, Gail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilkerson, William S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilkerson, William S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148